        "narrative_summary": "The APC c.487C>T variant creates a nonsense change (p.Gln163*) that truncates the APC protein. It has been reported in the context of colorectal cancer, a disease in which APC alterations are a well‑established driver.\n\nIn a targeted sequencing study of colorectal cancer patients, the c.487C>T change was identified as a somatic mutation in the tumor DNA, although the authors did not provide an explicit interpretation of its clinical significance [PMC11264515].\n\nAn evolutionary analysis of termination codons listed APC c.487C>T among a set of nonsense mutations that generate a stop codon, confirming that the substitution converts the codon for glutamine to a TAG stop codon (p.Gln163*) [PMC10471768]. No experimental functional assays were reported.\n\nTaken together, the available evidence demonstrates that APC c.487C>T produces a premature termination codon and occurs as a somatic event in colorectal cancer, but there is no direct clinical classification, functional validation, population frequency data, or computational prediction presented. Consequently, the pathogenicity of this variant remains uncertain; it is consistent with a loss‑of‑function alteration in APC, yet definitive evidence to support a pathogenic or benign designation is lacking.",
